Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.49,0:22:40.72,Background,,0,0,0,,They will both get captured if they move.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.85,0:22:43.85,Background,,0,0,0,,But if they don't move, then they don't get captured.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.91,0:22:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have a Seki, leave it be until the end of the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.05,0:22:49.77,NoteArial_Igo,,0,0,0,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&\fad(417,501)\3c&H018A0A&\4c&H018A0A&\fscx98\fscy85\bord1.5\shad0.5\pos(320,278)}If a Seki forms, the game ends with the seki.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.05,0:22:49.77,NoteArial_Igo,,0,0,0,,{\fs22\1c&HFFFFFF&\fad(417,501)\3c&H018A0A&\4c&H018A0A&\fscx98\fscy100\bord1.5\shad0.5\pos(319,356)}Neither side can count the Seki as their own territory
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.98,0:22:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not counted for either side as a territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.02,0:22:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Seki seems difficult, but it's a way to avoid\Ngetting captured when you're about to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.04,0:22:55.11,NoteArial_Igo,,0,0,0,,{\fs29\1c&HFFFFFF&\fad(167,0)\3c&H1300EF&\4c&HFFFFFF&\fscx99\fscy100\bord3\shad1\move(305,265,305,304)}To be continued...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.11,0:22:57.33,NoteArial_Igo,,0,0,0,,{\fs29\1c&HFFFFFF&\fad(0,0)\3c&H1300EF&\4c&HFFFFFF&\fscx99\fscy100\bord3\shad1\pos(305,304)}To be continued...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.02,0:23:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Touya Meijin's retiring!?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.19,0:23:03.25,Background,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about? I can't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.95,0:23:05.42,Background,,0,0,0,,Why did he retire?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.06,0:23:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Why!?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.25,0:23:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No fair! It's too early!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.07,0:23:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't taken a title from Touya Meijin yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.59,0:23:26.76,Background,,0,0,0,,What a self-centered man you are, Touya Kouyou.
